_decoded_content.name: Toothbrush Toothpaste Aid
_decoded_content.description:
This piece of assistive technology can be used to stabilize a toothbrush on a surface while applying toothpaste. It can be helpful for individuals without the use of both upper extremities during this daily task. 

This is a remix of WhyAndHow's design. I was very impressed with the original design, but I needed to do some sanding due to sharp edges.  

Use a heat gun or print with thin layers to avoid bacterial build up between layers. 
Be sure to wash the item frequently with warm water and soap.

Use a filament that you perceive to be food safe after completing your research.

_decoded_content.details:
Summary

This piece of assistive technology can be used to stabilize a toothbrush on a surface while applying toothpaste. It can be helpful for individuals without the use of both upper extremities during this daily task.

This is a remix of WhyAndHow's design. I was very impressed with the original design, but I needed to do some sanding due to sharp edges.

Use a heat gun or print with thin layers to avoid bacterial build up between layers.
Be sure to wash the item frequently with warm water and soap.

Use a filament that you perceive to be food safe after completing your research.

Print Settings

Printer:

Monoprice Voxel 3d Printer 

                                            <p class="detail-setting rafts"><strong>Rafts: </strong>                     <div><p>No</p></div></p>                                                                                <p class="detail-setting supports"><strong>Supports: </strong>                     <div><p>No</p></div></p>                                                                                <p class="detail-setting infill"><strong>Infill: </strong>                     <div><p>20</p></div></p>

Post-Printing

Please be sure to double check for any sharp edges/corners before using this device.
I also used gorilla glue to stick a piece of Dycem on the bottom. The Dycem provides a non-slip surface but still allows for regular cleaning of the surfaces. You can put this on any "non-slip" surface, like shelf liner.

How I Designed This

I used TinkerCad to round the corners.
